title: 'Stubborn' swan blocks M27 at Fareham - BBC News
text:
'Stubborn' swan blocks M27 at Fareham 21 February 2017 Image caption The bird blocked two lanes on the eastbound carriageway A "stubborn" swan caused a bottleneck on the M27 in Hampshire after blocking two lanes. 
Highways England tweeted a picture of the bird which swanned onto the eastbound carriageway at junction 11, near Fareham, at about 08:00 GMT. 
After a failed attempt to fly away the swan was rescued and "safely taken away", it said. 
Hampshire Police said officers were called to the scene and are in touch with Swan Lifeline and the RSPCA. 
Highways England tweeted : "Two lanes are closed on the #M27 eastbound within J11 due to a stubborn swan on the carriageway!"
